Initial Capture of patient demographics information\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ 
	Name: CapturePatientDemographics
	Particiapting Actors:
		MD User (Nurse, Secretary, Refereing MD, Radiologist)
	Entry Conditions: Reference logs in the the system.
	Flow of events:
		1. MD User logs in to the system with their supplied HIS/RIS ID and Password.
		2. The System logs them in to thier respective portal.
		3. Radiologist/Referring Physician selects add new patient or update returning patient.
		4. The System loads the new Add Patient form.
		5. Radiologist/Referring Physician fills out created form with new/returning patient's current demographics..
		6. The System sends the form information to the database for archiving.
	Exit Conditions: Once the system has saved the patient demographics the the database and recives confimration of archival.
	Exceptions:
		1a. User credientials are not valid.
			1a1. The System displays an error message.
		2a. The System cannot connect to the database.
			2a1. The System displays an error message.
	Quality Requirments: The MD User must be informed of any exceptional cases.
   
Referring Physician/Radiologist orders the desired radiology procedure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
	Name: OrderRadiologyProcedure
	Particiapting Actors:
		MD User (Refereing MD, Radiologist)
	Entry Conditions: MD User selects request radiology modality for patient in radiology Tab
	Flow of events:
		1. Radiologist/Referring Physician accesses radiology portal
		2. The System loads the respective radiology portal
		3. Radiologist/Referring Physician selects modality Tab
		4. The System loads the modality Tab
		5. Radiologist/Referring Physician selects desired modality 
		6. Requests scheduling of modality resources.  
    Exit Conditions: The MD user must confirm request of modality resources
    Exceptions:
		5a. Modality unavailable, flags are thrown
		5b. Patient conflicts, flags are thrown
    Quality Requirments: The System must flag the MD if any conflicts are found and will continue with MD user approval.
	
System prefetchs prior patient studies\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
	Name: fetchPriorStudies
	Particiapting Actors:
		System
		Modality Technition
	Entry Conditions: Modality Techinition begins scheduled procedure
	Flow of events:
		1. The modality technition begins the scheduled modality
		2. The system automatically accesses the image archival database and collects every prior study of the patient and sends the images to the diagnostic workstation
    Exit Conditions: The system retrieves the images
    Exceptions:
		1a. The modality technition never begins the modality procedure
			1a1. The system will then not connact the archival database
		2a. The System cannot contact the archival database
			2a1. The system throws a flag and displays an error.
		2b. The patient has no prior studies conducted
			2b1. The system displays "No Patient Studies Found"
    Quality Requirments: The System must display any warning for system technitions to debug 

Modality worklist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
	Name: CreateModalityWorklist
	Particiapting Actors: 
		System
	Entry Conditions: 
	Flow of events:
		1. The System updates the global schedule with patient and his/her procudure information.
		2. All modality imaging machinary will have access to thier respective scheduling information
    Exit Conditions: The database has been updated with new patient and procedure information
    Exceptions:
		1a. The system fails to update the global schedule due to some error
			1a1. The system will then display an error
    Quality Requirments: The System must flag the MD if any conflicts are found and will continue with MD user approval.       
 
Charge Capture \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
	Name: ChargeCapture
	Particiapting Actors: 
		Patient
		System
		Secretary
	Entry Conditions: The patient signs in at the front desk
	Flow of events:
		1. The system keeps track of the patients expenses.
		2. Expenses accrue as procedures are completed.
		3. The Patient interacts with the secretary to secure charge capture.
    Exit Conditions: The Secretary has flag the system to stop charge capture for patient
    Exceptions:
		1a. The system fails to update charge capture for patient
    Quality Requirments: The System must flag for all falied captures
    
Modality image Archiving\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
	Name: ArchiveModalityImage
	Particiapting Actors: 
		System
		Modality Techintion
	Entry Conditions: Modality Techinition begins scheduled procedure
	Flow of events:
		1. The Modality Techintion begins scheduled modality 
		2. The system does fetchPriorStudies use case as technitions takes modality images
		3. Modality Technitions can either accept or not accepted taken modality image and has the ability to take more images if needed
		4. The system will automatically save all approved modality images and store them within an archival database under the patient id and patient name
		5. The system amkes the recent aquistions available to PACS.
    Exit Conditions: The modality technition ends scheduled procedure
    Exceptions:
		1a. The system fails to update charge capture for patient
    Quality Requirments: The System must load and display taken images instantly
 
Diagnositic Workstation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
	Name: WorkstationDiagnostics
	Particiapting Actors: 
		Radiologist
		System
    Entry Conditions: The Radiologist signs in and accesses the diagnotics workstation tab              
	Basic Flow of events:
		1. The system will automatically load in prefetched patient studies for radiologist viewing and 
		2. Any new patient studies will automatically be accessable to radiologist
		3. The radiologist writes their report.
		4. The system archives the report to Report Repository with patient demographics infomration and patient modality images.
	Exit Conditions: The system confirms archival or report
	Exceptions:
    1a. If chosen, report and all relevant data/images can be physically printed   
	Quality Requirments: The radilogist must have access to patient images 
    
